entry.title: [relaunch_notification] Fix incorrect deadline in UX
entry.content:
The deadline to force a restart can be revised after an initial

notification is shown in certain situations. The wrong value could be

used for the dialog title in situations such as:



- The user is shown the dialog and dismisses it.

- All browser windows are deactivated.

- Something happens to change the deadline (e.g., the notification

period policy is changed).

- A browser window is activated.



This CL contains two fixes that could contribute to this bad user

experience:



1. The cached deadline is unconditionally updated. This will prevent a

stale deadline from being used.

2. UpgradeDetector no longer clears the deltas for the annoyance level

once the highest level is reached. This could cause its

GetAnnoyanceLevelDeadline method to return zeros.



Also in this CL:



- A DCHECK for negative deltas is added to the dialog title computation

so that we can (hopefully) spot if this happens via other means in the

wild.

- RelaunchNotificationControllerUiTest.ReactivateAfterDeadline is added

as a regression test for this bug.

- The platform_impl_ member of the RelaunchNotificationController class

is moved to the proper location the class decl according to style.

- Some questionable uses of Time in tests have been fixed.

entry.title: Deflake ContentAnalysisPrintBrowserTest.SystemPrintFromPrintPreview
entry.content:
This test involved two different waits, one for content analysis

scanning and another for the printing events. Differences in the

order of callbacks could result in deadlock when expected events had

already happened before waiting to see them occur.



Remove this possibility by modifying scanning to be another event in

the printing sequence and removing WaitOnScanning(). With only one

wait the order of such events no longer matter, so long as the correct

entry.title: Revert "Enable *building* of Rusty QR Code Generation on Android and Linux."
entry.content:
This reverts commit 2671028503c2e374dc354a8ebb090c62ca8299de.



Reason for revert: Breaks building chrome in the ChromeOS chroot



Original change's description:

> Enable *building* of Rusty QR Code Generation on Android and Linux.

>

> This CL enables *building* of Rusty QR Code Generation on the same

> platforms and configs where `enable_rust_crash` is built. It changes

> both `enable_rust_qr` and `enable_rust_base_conversions`, because

> QR-related FFI requires conversions from `base::span` into

> `rust::Slice`.

>

> This CL does *not* yet *use* Rusty QR Code Generation at runtime,

> because the "RustyQrCodeGenerator" feature remains disabled by default.

>

> Since this CL starts to include the `third_party/rust/qr_code` library,

> it expectedly leads to a ~22kB binary size increase. This increase has

> been reviewed and approved when the ATLs have reviewed landing of the

> third-party library (see https://crrev.com/c/4497329 and the approvals

> listed from that other CL's description). Also note that evaluating the

> binary size impact of shipping Rust code is tricky, because the cost of

> the base C++ libraries is amortized across multiple components, while

> the cost of the base Rust libraries will initially only support the QR

> crate.

>

> This CL modifies `testing/scripts/check_static_initializers.py` so that

> allowlist patterns span not only a filename, but also the symbol which

> brings in a static initializer. This should be more robust in general,

> but this also helps to work around a symbolization problem where Rust

> symbols are not associated with a filename in the `nacl_helper` binary

> (the `chrome` binary seems ok). For more details see

> https://crbug.com/1455186.

>

> Bug: 1431991

> Binary-Size: Size increase is unavoidable (see above).

> Change-Id: Id9224c349400d2421614a698b823e8469c15ac67

> Auto-Submit: Åukasz Anforowicz

entry.title: Pass AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource to external delegate.
entry.content:
When suggestions are queried, once they are retrieved successfully, the

external delegate's OnSuggestionsReturned() function is called. It is

responsible for forwarding the suggestions to the popup controller,

which then displays them. (Retrieving suggestions can be async, due to

a database query, e.g. in the case of autocomplete-the-feature)



Right now, one of the function's parameters is of type

AutoselectFirstSuggestion (strong alias for bool). It's set to true when

the suggestions were triggered by pressing the down arrow key.



Like in crrev.com/c/4552038 AutoselectFirstSuggestion can be derived

from the AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource. This CL replaces the

AutoselectFirstSuggestion parameter with

AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource. The follow-up CL will further refactor

the call path, and instead of passing a AutoselectFirstSuggestion to the

popup controller, the AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource will be passed on.

This makes it possible to derive the correct AutofillTriggerSource (not

AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource) when selecting a suggestions. See

crrev.com/c/4562174 and discussion there.



Technically, this is just replacing AutoselectFirstSuggestion with

AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource in a lot of places. When suggestions are

loaded async, an existing mechanism is reused to temporarily store the

suggestion trigger source (see SuggestionsHandler::QueryHandler in

single_field_form_filler). See CL comments for interesting changes.



In most unit tests, AutoselectFirstSuggestion is set to false. These

occurrences are replaced by

AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource::kFormControlElementClicked. This is the

most common suggestion trigger source and implies

AutoselectFirstSuggestion false (true corresponds to

kTextFieldDidReceiveKeyDown).



used in the renderer process and thus the suggestion_properties don't

apply. The values are simply added to a switch in the NOTREACHED() case.

entry.title: Fix crash when saving an address to the account in transport mode
entry.content:
Repro:

* Enable SyncEnableContactInfoDataTypeInTransportMode

(chrome://flags#replace-sync-promos-with-sign-in-promos does the

trick).

* Sign in, but don't enable Sync.

* Try to save an address.



Result: DCHECK at

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/main:components/autofill/core/browser/autofill_save_update_address_profile_delegate_ios.cc;drc=20911ffd8a0e1636801ddf303c17375fdedf9c83;l=93

because there is no syncing_user_email.



There were several issues:

* In transport mode, there is no ConsentLevel::kSync account.

* syncer::AUTOFILL is the wrong data type to check; addresses are

AUTOFILL_PROFILE or CONTACT_INFO.

* IsDataTypeActive() is probably the wrong thing to check? This only

becomes true once Sync has finished initializing and is actively

running (hence "active"), but presumably a save-to-account action

can happen before Sync is fully ready?



The first of these affects transport mode only, but the other two

affect full-Sync mode too.



This CL fixes the issues by:

* Changing from ConsentLevel::kSync to kSignin.

* Removing the data-type-active check.



This is safe, since the logic for deciding whether to upload an

address to GAS lives elsewhere anyway.

entry.title: Displaying space instead of line and paragraph separators
entry.content:
Chrome renders line separator (0x2028) and paragraph separator (0x2029)

as either a missing glyph or l-sep/p-sep symbol on various platforms.



On Android this happens due to the lack of the glyphs in Android system

fonts, so it is displayed as a missing glyph. Windows system fonts have

l-sep and p-sep symbols for the 0x2028 and 0x2029 codepoints

respectively. On Mac OS these glyphs are being synthesized, see [0].



According to unicode specification line separator and paragraph

separator should be displayed as space, compare [1].

entry.title: Inherit COOP: restrict-properties and un-suppress opener
entry.content:
To make the `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: restrict-properties` (COOP:RP)

more useful, we'd like to let cross-origin iframes inherit this policy

from their parent and keep the opener connection between windows that

the iframes open. See

https://github.com/hemeryar/coi-with-popups/blob/main/docs/cross_origin_iframe_popup.MD

for more explanations.



In https://crrev.com/c/4404116, we've bundled the origin that sets the

COOP with the policy. This CL is to use the stored origin in COOP

algorithms:

1. In `RenderFrameHostImpl::DidCommitNewDocument`, we let embedded

documents inherit the COOP:RP bundle when the policy is COOP:RP.

2. To keep the opener connection, we return false in

`COOPSuppressOpener` when COOP value is RP.

3. Since we allow the popup's initial empty document and its subframes

to stay in the process, we had to restrict its crossOriginIsolated

capability. Otherwise, a cross-origin iframe can get around permission

policy that restricts it from using crossOriginIsolated APIs.

- For the initial empty document, we pass a boolean to the renderer

via CreateNewWindow.

- For the subframes of the initial empty document, we pass a boolean

via CommitNavigation.



This CL also adds new test cases for

1. Cross-origin iframe opener v.s. same-origin iframe opener.

2. Checking the popup's subframe's `crossOriginIsolated`.

3. Checking popup's `crossOriginIsolated` after it navigates away from

the initial empty document. (This is to make sure that we don't

restrict the `crossOriginIsolated` when we shouldn't)

entry.title: [capture_mode] Add support for multiplanar SI to CameraVideoFrameHandler
entry.content:
This CL adds support for non-legacy multiplanar SharedImages to

CameraVideoFrameHandler. This means that there are now three codepaths

in CameraVideoFrameHandler that deal with multiplanar SharedImages:



* Creating a single SharedImage with format MultiPlaneFormat::kNV12

(new codepath that is used when kMultiPlaneVideoCaptureSharedImages

is enabled and IsMultiPlaneFormatForHardwareVideoEnabled() is true)

* Creating one SharedImage for each of the two NV12 planes (existing

codepath that is used when kMultiPlaneVideoCaptureSharedImages is

enabled and IsMultiPlaneFormatForHardwareVideoEnabled() is false)

* Creating one SharedImage for which external sampling is performed (

existing codepath that is used when

kMultiPlaneVideoCaptureSharedImages is false)



kMultiPlaneVideoCaptureSharedImages is not enabled on ChromeOS but is

enabled by default on Windows and Mac, where this code will shortly be

used.



Bug: 1454406
